tion can obtain to those doors, or do I need to bring a rogue along with me to pick the locks?  I'm hoping that there are keys, cause the rest of my guild isn't too keen on giving up one of their favorite hunting grounds, even if the rewards are pretty nice.<br><br>Third....everything in Chardok is on Brood of Di'Zok faction, correct?  Including the undead, golems, etc?  Having good faction should allow me full access without any places needing to be avoided, right?  I ask this because I know that Halfling rogues of Brell are not KOS to most things in The Hole, but there are some things in there (rats, undead) that they are KOS to, and I want to take the time while I have good faction to explore as much of Chardok as I can....I am eventually gonna have to kill in there again, as I still don't have my blade from the Queen, and this most definitely gonna ruin my faction. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br>Any other tidbits that may be important that I may have forgotten I would be greatly appreciated of having.<br><br> <p><center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38110">Knord Rainhater</a></b><br>60 Barbarian Warlord<br><a href="http://pub58.ezboard.com/bravenswings">Ravens Wings</a> Guild Leader<br><a href="http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg">The Tribunal</a><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1154<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/11/02 7:59:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chardok quests...a few questions</span><hr size=1> 1.  i duno where the traps are, why?   not like you need to worry about it breaking your invis if you have faction<br><br>2.  1 locked door with no keys are the least of your worries.  lot harder parts to get in the quest than finding a rogue.  (i followed down another guild's raid)<br><br>3.  nothing will attack you if you have faction <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucslochraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/14/02 6:46:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chardok quests...a few questions</span><hr size=1> The bridge with the trap is on the way to Korocust's room.  The room with the sparkling red ball, interrogators.  It's actually a screwed up trap.  Sometimes it never goes off.  Sometimes it's a gravity flux type of thing.  Usually it is a frost AOE spell for 241.  I like to stand there and take damage while I work my bind wound.  Nothing to worry about really.<br><br>There is also a trap on bridge that goes to castle.  It triggers several undead mobs.  But if you arent kos then you won't trigger the undead...just the trap message.<br><br>1 locked door and you need rogue to get through.  You won't need to go to royalty for a long time anyway so don't worry about it.<br><br>Everything is KOS.  However the mobs outside are Collective and unless you turn in tons and tons of salts/skins you'll stay KOS to them because goblins don't give any hits for Collective.<br><br> <p><b>Lochraven<b><br>Warlord<br>The Nameless</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubaadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baadan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.magelo.com/res/eq/itemicon/0011.png" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 4:21:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Chardok quests...a few questions</span><hr size=1> I have a question too...<br><br><br>I intend on doing the 3 Chardok quests, unfortunantly...the Chardok Queen is a part of our epic and I assume killing her would hurt my faction quite a bit.<br><br>Should I avoid Chardok raids until I get the quests done and then start joining Chardok raids to get the Queen's peice?<br><br>I have done a bit of work and collected some skins and salts from Nurga (or Droga...can't remember which one) but I have no idea what my faction is it in Chardok atm.<br><br>I'm actually thinking I should go ahead and keep on raiding Chardok as little as possible, but doing it when I need to to get my epic peice, trying to avoid losing faction as much as possible, and then working faction up once I'm done killing in Chardok for the most part so I can recharge the 2nd ring.<br><br>So should I raid Chardok now, get epic peice, then faction later? Or faction now, raid Chardok, then do a bit more faction work to get up to ally so I can recharge my 2nd ring? <p><hr width="267" align="left"><table  width="*" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1"><tr><td  align="center"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168211" target="new"><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/baadansig1