lp with royal raids a ton! You will be very helpful with CR, scouting, and you can hail pull the queen single.<br><br>On the other hand, is your guild going to let you loot that queen blade if you don't actually participate in meleeing her to death? Figure that one out first. Once you do Chardok faction, you really don't want to kill there anymore. I double boxed my way to ally faction, my warrior was at bottomed out and it took 2000 faction hits to get to threatening! It took almost that many (1800-2000) to go from threatening to ally. That's going to be a lot of wasted effort if you trash your Chardok faction on a royals raid... if you're going to ruin it, don't bother wasting your time trying to get Chardok faction now. <p><p><map name="FPMap0"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=207958" shape="rect" coords="98, 46, 245, 84"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=240522" shape="rect" coords="276, 49, 407, 86"><area href="http://www.dragonsfang.com/revolution/" shape="rect" coords="168, 8, 349, 46"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=240522" coords="411, 3, 497, 86" shape="rect"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=207958" shape="rect" coords="4, 3, 93, 86"></map><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/ssbbrothar/tamsig.jpg" usemap="#FPMap0" width="500" height="90"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usmushums.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smushums</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 1179<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/16/02 2:52:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chardok quests...a few questions</span><hr size=1> if you have the drusella part, knock out the entire quest all at once..<br><br>if you dont have the urn, id say work on your epic while you camp drusella.  you could go months between the time you have ally faction and the time you finally get the urn drop.  who knows how many royals raids your guild might try to do.<br><br>i have no idea how big of a hit you get from killin the queen, but most guilds that kill royals like to stay a few cycles and farm her.<br><br>i got sick of waiting for a chardok raid, and had to ask my guild leader to do it so i could finish my epic.  that night, i looted the queen.... and the next day i started in droga <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=7023  target="web">smushums<a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubalgothblackvoodoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balgoth Blackvoodoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/18/02 6:06:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Chardok quests...a few questions</span><hr size=1> He is right took me about 4 months to get the dragon sinew and urn....let alone to camp the angry goblin for the second ring.<br><br>Raid , ger your epic, and in the mean time camp juggs and drusilla.  Factioning will go alot faster if you have all the items to turn in once you hit ally =) <p><br><i><u><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172247>Ghworg</a></b></u></i></br>60 Warrior <br><i><u><b><a href=http://www.remedy.fr.st/>Remedy</a></b></u></i></br>The Nameless</p><i></i></td></t